.:: Puzzle 3x4-Level-4-11::.
The people use 4 different means of transport: quad-bike, roller, tram, taxi
4 different games are played: chess, poker, scrabble, go
City: prague, boston, hamburg, rome
1. the person driving the quad-bike is on the far left or far right##3
2. the person playing poker is on the left of the person playing chess##1
3. the person traveling to rome is on the left or right of the person playing scrabble##3
4. the person playing poker is in an even position##4
5. the person driving the tram is on the right of the person playing chess##1
6. the person traveling to rome is on the right of the person playing poker##1
7. the person traveling to boston is on the left of the person playing poker##1
8. the person driving the taxi is on the left or right of the person traveling to boston##3
9. the person driving the quad-bike is on the left of the person traveling to prague##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |         1          |     2     |      3      |    4    |
| Transport      | quad-bike                | taxi  | roller | tram   |
| Game           | go | poker | chess   | scrabble |
| City   | boston         | prague     | rome     | hamburg |

